Architecture.description: The hardware architecture for which the image was built for. The architecture can either be Intel (amd64) or Power (ppc64le).

Cmd.description:
The command and arguments in this list are passed to the container to be executed when the container is started. This command must be a long-running command. Do not use a short-lived command, for example, /bin/date, because it might cause the container to crash.
Sample long-running commands:
["ping","localhost"]
["tail","-f","/dev/null"]
["sh","-c","while true; do date; sleep 20; done"]

Domainmame.description: The domain name to be used for the container.

Entrypoint.description: The entrypoint specifies a command that will always be executed when the container starts.

Env.description: A list of environment variables in the form of key=value pairs. All keys in this list have to be unique. List multiple keys separately and if you include quotation marks, include them around both the environment variable name and the value.

ExposedPorts.description: A list of all udp and tcp ports that have been publicly exposed during the container creation.

Hostname.description: The host name of the container provided by Openstack.

Image.description: The unique ID of the image.

Labels.description: List of custom metadata that was added to the image. Labels serve a wide range of uses, such as adding notes or license requirements to an image. Every label is a key/ value pair.

OpenStdin.description: When set to true, it opens stdin.

StdinOnce.description: When set to true it closes stdin after the attached client disconnects.

Tty.description: When set to true, attach standard streams to a tty, including stdin if it is not closed.

User.description: The user to be used inside the container.

Volumes.description: Docker specific. Not supported by IBM Containers. The path to the volume that is created when deploying a container from the image. To use a volume in IBM Containers, you must first create a volume and then mount it to your container during creation.

WorkingDir.description: The working directory inside the container where specified commands are executed.

Created.description: The time when the image was created.

Id.description: Unique ID of the image that you inspected.

Parent.description: The ID of the parent image that was used to build this image.

Size.description: The real size of the image.

VirtualSize.description: The virtual size of the image.

Status.description: The current status of the container. The status can either be a transient one, such as BUILDING or NETWORKING, or a non-transient one, such as RUNNING, SHUTDOWN, CRASHED, or SUSPENDED.

Transient.description: When set to true, the current container state is temporary and will change soon. An example for a transient state is the BUILDING state. A container that is created will be set to the BUILDING state until all container layers are created and the container is started. When set to false, the container state is permanent, such as CRASHED.

Anti-affinity.description: If set to `true` the container instances in the group are spread across separate physical compute nodes, which reduces the likelihood of containers crashing due to hardware failures. If set to `false`, the container instances in the group share the same physical compute node.

Autorecovery.description: Can be either true or false. If set to true, the Autorecovery mode is enabled for your container group. In case a container instance crashes or stops, this instance is removed and a new one is automatically recreated. If set to false, the Autorecovery mode is disabled. In case a container instances crashes or stops, it is not automatically recreated by IBM Containers.

AvailabilityZone.description: Current IBM Containers availability zone on Openstack.

Cmd.description: The Docker command that was specified to be run when the container instances are started.

Creation_time.description: Timestamp when the container group was created.

Env.description: The list of environmental variables that were defined for the container group. Each environment variable consists of a unique key and a value.

Id.description: Unique identifier representing a specific container group.

Image.description: The unique ID of the container image your container group instances are based on.

ImageName.description: The full path to the container image in your private Bluemix repository.

Memory.description: The size of each container instance that runs in the container group in MegaByte.

Name.description: The name of the container group.

CurrentSize.description: The current number of container instances that are running in your container group.

Desired.description: The number of container instances that you require.

Max.description: The maximum number of container instance that you want to run in your container group.

Min.description: The minimum number of container instances that you want to run in your container group.

Port.description: The public port that has been exposed. If you specified a route, your container group is accessible from the Internet.

in_progress.description: Can be either true or false. If set to true, then the route is in the process of being mapped to the container group and set up in the GoRouter. Is set to false, then the set up of the route is completed.

successful.description: Can be either true or false. If set to true, then the route is successfully registrered with the GoRouter. If set to false, then the route registration has not yet finished yet or could not be completed without errors.

Routes.description: The public route that is mapped to the container group. When you expose a public port, you can use the route to access your container group from the Internet.

Status.description:
The current status of the container group. The container group status is a composite of ACTION and STATUS:

ACTIONS = (CREATE, DELETE, UPDATE, ROLLBACK, SUSPEND, RESUME, ADOPT, SNAPSHOT, CHECK, RESTORE)

STATUSES = (IN_PROGRESS, FAILED, COMPLETE)

UpdatedTime.description: Timestamp when the container group was updated. If the container group was not updated before, `null` is returned.

Volumes.description: List of volumes to be associated with the container, in the format of volume name:path:mode where mode can be ro or rw.
